Because H100 offers higher raw performance and larger memory plus new hardware features that speed deep-learning computation. In the provided text the H100 is highlighted because:
- it has more memory, enabling larger batch sizes and thus higher throughput;  
- the Hopper/H100 adds the Tensor Memory Accelerator (TMA) and improved Tensor Cores/asynchronous memory copies, which accelerate matrix multiplies and reduce per-thread indexing overhead;  
- the H100 SXM is noted as cost‑effective with very strong performance for datacenter use.

(As a caveat in the context, NVIDIA’s published H100 numbers also used larger batch sizes and different GPU counts, so some reported gains reflect those benchmarking choices.)
